    dc:creator "Worthy, Robert; González, Jorge M.; Ríos, Sergio D." ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "A review of the genus Insigniocastnia J. Y. Miller, 2007 (Lepidoptera: Castniidae) with notes on Castnia amalthaea H. Druce, 1890" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625371>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625373>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625375> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625371>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–12. Castnia amalthaea H. Druce, 1890, Figs. 1, 2: ♀ holotype, C. amalthaea, “Brazil” (Courtesy NHMUK); Figs. 3, 4: ♂ holotype, C. wagneri Le Cerf, 1911, Misiones, Argentina (Courtesy MNHN); Fig. 5: ♂, C. amalthaea, Patquia, Argentina (Courtesy MLPA); Fig. 6: ♂, C. amalthaea, La Rioja, Argentina (Courtesy TP); Fig. 7: ♂ holotype, C. minerva R. Krüger, 1926, Paraguay (Courtesy NHMUK); Fig. 8: ♂ paratype, C. minerva, Paraguay (Courtesy NHMUK); Fig. 9: ♀ [?], C. amalthaea, Formosa, Argentina (Courtesy MLPA); Fig. 10–12: ♂♂, C. amalthaea, Santiago del Estero, Argentina, (RW collection). Scale: 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625371/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625373>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Distribution map of all known collecting localities of Castnia amalthaea, collected and identified as any of its synonyms. Black dots represent collected specimens, the open circle represents a sighting. Note: the type locality of C. amalthaea could be anywhere in southeast Brazil, so is not included (map prepared by Bolívar R. Garcete, MNHN Paraguay)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625373/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2625375>
    dc:description "FIGURES 14–15. Habitat of Castnia amalthaea in the Gran Chaco, Argentina. Note that the forest is a generally open, scrubby area. (Photos: Alejandro Borquez & Carlos Calderón). Figure 16: C. amalthaea resting on leaf of Caraguata, Bromelia cf. serra (Bromeliaceae), chaco forest remnant, Departamento de Presidente Hayes, Paraguay (Photo: Sergio D. Ríos)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2625375/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

